{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d09b1e7d-4c19-499f-ad4b-7ef1bcd707b6","content":"Here's what you need to change to upgrade to MSTest v3:\n\n**1. In `TestProject.csproj`:**\n\n- **Remove** the assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n- **Add** the `MSTest` v3 meta-package (which bundles the test framework + adapter)\n- **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\nReplace your `<ItemGroup>` sections with:\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n  <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.12.0\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n**2. In `OrderServiceTests.cs`:**\n\nNo changes needed — MSTest v3 still uses the `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace, and `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `[Timeout]`, and `Assert` all work the same way.\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n| Before | After |\n|--------|-------|\n| Assembly ref to `QualityTools.UnitTestFramework` | NuGet `MSTest` 3.8.3 |\n| `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` 17.5.0 | `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` 17.12.0 |\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"19665275-81ee-40a3-8273-05b3a14526b8","outputTokens":349,"requestId":"63CF:16EF68:3B4247B:416F4BA:6A02FA4B"},"id":"351d9174-7525-4d1b-907d-f9899ecca26c","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:00:59.618Z","parentId":"348a2b8e-d31e-4363-affd-6f1769275bb0"}
